{"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"RegexRef","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"After instantiating a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GRegex"},{"text":", you can use its methods to find matches","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in a string, replace matches within a string, or split the string at matches.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"GRegex","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" implements regular expression pattern matching using syntax and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"semantics (such as character classes, quantifiers, and capture groups)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"similar to Perl regular expression. See the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"man:pcre2pattern(3)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" for details.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A typical scenario for regex pattern matching is to check if a string","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"matches a pattern. The following statements implement this scenario."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"{ .c }","code":["const char *regex_pattern = \".*GLib.*\";","const char *string_to_search = \"You will love the GLib implementation of regex\";","`g_autoptr(GMatchInfo)` match_info = NULL;","`g_autoptr(GRegex)` regex = NULL;","","regex = g_regex_new (regex_pattern, G_REGEX_DEFAULT, G_REGEX_MATCH_DEFAULT, NULL);","g_assert (regex != NULL);","","if (g_regex_match (regex, string_to_search, G_REGEX_MATCH_DEFAULT, &match_info))","  {","    int start_pos, end_pos;","    g_match_info_fetch_pos (match_info, 0, &start_pos, &end_pos);","    g_print (\"Match successful! Overall pattern matches bytes `d` to `d`\\n\", start_pos, end_pos);","  }","else","  {","    g_print (\"No match!\\n\");","  }"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The constructor for ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GRegex"},{"type":"text","text":" includes two sets of bitmapped flags:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"[flags"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexCompileFlags"},{"type":"text","text":"]—These flags"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"control how GLib compiles the regex. There are options for case"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"sensitivity, multiline, ignoring whitespace, etc.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"[flags"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexMatchFlags","isActive":true},{"text":"]—These flags control","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"GRegex","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"’s matching behavior, such as anchoring and customizing definitions","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"for newline characters.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Some regex patterns include backslash assertions, such as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\\d"},{"text":" (digit) or","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\\D"},{"type":"text","text":" (non-digit). The regex pattern must escape those backslashes. For"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"example, the pattern ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"\\\\d\\\\D\""},{"text":" matches a digit followed by a non-digit.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"GLib’s implementation of pattern matching includes a "},{"code":"start_position","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"argument for some of the match, replace, and split methods. Specifying"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a start position provides flexibility when you want to ignore the first"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"n","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" characters of a string, but want to incorporate backslash assertions"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"at character ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"n","type":"text"}]},{"text":" - 1. For example, a database field contains inconsistent","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"spelling for a job title: ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"healthcare provider"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"health-care provider"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The database manager wants to make the spelling consistent by adding a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"hyphen when it is missing. The following regex pattern tests for the string"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"care","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" preceded by a non-word boundary character (instead of a hyphen)","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and followed by a space.","type":"text"}]},{"code":["const char *regex_pattern = \"\\\\Bcare\\\\s\";"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"{ .c }"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"An efficient way to match with this pattern is to start examining at","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"start_position","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" 6 in the string "},{"code":"healthcare","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"code":"health-care","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"{ .c }","code":["const char *regex_pattern = \"\\\\Bcare\\\\s\";","const char *string_to_search = \"healthcare provider\";","`g_autoptr(GMatchInfo)` match_info = NULL;","`g_autoptr(GRegex)` regex = NULL;","","regex = g_regex_new (","  regex_pattern,","  G_REGEX_DEFAULT,","  G_REGEX_MATCH_DEFAULT,","  NULL);","g_assert (regex != NULL);","","g_regex_match_full (","  regex,","  string_to_search,","  -1,","  6, \/\/ position of 'c' in the test string.","  G_REGEX_MATCH_DEFAULT,","  &match_info,","  NULL);"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The method [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.Regex.match_full"},{"text":"] (and other methods implementing","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"start_pos"},{"text":") allow for lookback before the start position to determine if","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the previous character satisfies an assertion.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Unless you set the [flags"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.RegexCompileFlags.RAW"},{"text":"] as one of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the ","type":"text"},{"code":"GRegexCompileFlags","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", all the strings passed to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GRegex"},{"text":" methods must","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"be encoded in UTF-8. The lengths and the positions inside the strings are","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"in bytes and not in characters, so, for instance, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\\xc3\\xa0"},{"text":" (i.e., ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"à"},{"text":")","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"is two bytes long but it is treated as a single character. If you set","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_REGEX_RAW"},{"text":", the strings can be non-valid UTF-8 strings and a byte is","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"treated as a character, so "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\\xc3\\xa0"},{"text":" is two bytes and two characters long.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Regarding line endings, ","type":"text"},{"code":"\\n","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" matches a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\\n"},{"text":" character, and ","type":"text"},{"code":"\\r","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" matches"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"a "},{"code":"\\r","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" character. More generally, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\\R"},{"text":" matches all typical line endings:","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"CR + LF (","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\\r\\n"},{"text":"), LF (linefeed, U+000A, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\\n"},{"text":"), VT (vertical tab, U+000B,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\\v"},{"text":"), FF (formfeed, U+000C, ","type":"text"},{"code":"\\f","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"), CR (carriage return, U+000D, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\\r"},{"text":"),","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"NEL (next line, U+0085), LS (line separator, U+2028), and PS (paragraph"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"separator, U+2029)."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The behaviour of the dot, circumflex, and dollar metacharacters are"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"affected by newline characters. By default, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GRegex"},{"text":" matches any newline","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"character matched by ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\\R"},{"type":"text","text":". You can limit the matched newline characters by"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"specifying the [flags"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.RegexMatchFlags.NEWLINE_CR"},{"text":"],","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[flags","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.RegexMatchFlags.NEWLINE_LF","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"], and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[flags"},{"code":"GLib.RegexMatchFlags.NEWLINE_CRLF","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] compile options, and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with [flags"},{"code":"GLib.RegexMatchFlags.NEWLINE_ANY","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"],"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[flags"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.RegexMatchFlags.NEWLINE_CR"},{"type":"text","text":"],"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[flags","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.RegexMatchFlags.NEWLINE_LF"},{"text":"] and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[flags"},{"code":"GLib.RegexMatchFlags.NEWLINE_CRLF","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"] match options.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"These settings are also relevant when compiling a pattern if"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[flags"},{"code":"GLib.RegexCompileFlags.EXTENDED","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] is set and an unescaped"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"#","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" outside a character class is encountered. This indicates a comment"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that lasts until after the next newline."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Because ","type":"text"},{"code":"GRegex","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" does not modify its internal state between creation and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"destruction, you can create and modify the same "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GRegex"},{"type":"text","text":" instance from"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"different threads. In contrast, [struct","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MatchInfo"},{"text":"] is not thread safe.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The regular expression low-level functionalities are obtained through","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the excellent "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"http:\/\/www.pcre.org\/"},{"type":"text","text":" library written by Philip Hazel."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexRef","isActive":true},{"text":" type acts as a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying ","type":"text"},{"code":"GRegex","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It exposes methods that can operate on this data type through "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexProtocol","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" conformance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexRef","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" only as an "},{"code":"unowned","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" reference to an existing ","type":"text"},{"code":"GRegex","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Regex","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" (instead of "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexRef","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":") if you want to use Automatic Reference Counting for memory management of the underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GRegex"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Note"}]}],"metadata":{"title":"RegexRef","symbolKind":"struct","roleHeading":"Structure","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"role":"symb